postcontent: Custom built Patriot Ordinance Factory .308 with 20" Nitride Heated Deep Fluted barrel. Semi-automatic with three position short-stroke gas piston system. Nickel-Boron coated bolt carrier group, chrome plated bolt, Teflon receiver with tension screws. Ambidextrous bolt release, safety selector and bolt catch. Replaced collapsible stock and proprietary buffer tube with custom buffer assembly to include matched weighted buffer spring to accommodate the Magpul PRS stock. Shipping as is with a Vortex Viper 6.5-20X, 50mm objective lens with mil dot reticle and medium height Vortex matched 30mm steel rings. The optic also has a Vortex brand sunshade and a set of Butler Creek scope caps. Additionally shipping with Harris 6-9inch swivel bipod mounted on a GG&G Harris bipod adapter, a Butler creek padded two point sling, two steel 20rd DPMS mags, and two Gen2 20rd PMAGs. Barrel is well maintained with a grand total of 450 rounds through it. Didn't swap out the POF drop in trigger system but with a smooth 4.5 lbs., there wasn't reason to. She's a tack driver out to 900m with a steady hand and hand loaded rounds. Built the buffer system myself from scratch to get the perfect amount of pressure going back into the BCG. The one thing is she's picky about ammo so I greatly encourage hand loads to maximize performance. Personally I don't suggest running anything larger than 168g unless you run a suppressor instead of the factory triple ported muzzle break. You also might want to consider running it suppressed or investing in some good ear protection; she's about as loud as a standard length .338 bolt gun. Very balanced with surprisingly good recoil mitigation for a 20" Piston .308.

postcontent: The P-Series are short recoil–operated, locked breech semi-automatic pistols. They utilize a SIG P220 type locking system, and an M1911-style tilting barrel. The P-Series were made with a traditional double-action/single-action (DA/SA) trigger mechanism.The standard models have an ambidextrous manual safety/decocker located on the slide; when the safety lever is lowered to the safe position, the firing pin is cammed into the slide away from the hammer, the trigger is disconnected from the sear and the hammer is decocked. When the lever is released the firing pin springs back to the normal position. All models feature an automatic firing pin safety that blocks the firing pin unless the trigger is pulled fully rearward.Nearly all internal parts, including the barrel, are stainless steel; while the slide and ejector are carbon steel. The P85 uses an investment cast aluminum frame.The 9mm version uses a double-column box magazine and has a 15 round capacity. The magazine release located behind the trigger guard, it can be pushed forward from either side to eject the magazine.Developed in Israel for the world's military and special services. The combat proven Fobus Concealed Carry Holster is a revolutionary step forward in holster design and technology. Fobus is the first manufacturer of injection molded polymer holsters, with this experience Fobus is the leader in high-density space age polymer, with the more models and the most fits in the market place. Comfort is vital when carrying concealed, Fobus designers have delivered  holsters that weigh 2 ounces. These holsters are high riding, close fitting, with a low profile, have a rubberized paddle for comfort, steel reinforced rivet attachment system for durability. They are rugged and reliable and virtually maintenance free. Fobus holsters utilizes a passive retention system that allows for rapid presentation.
